name: openmmforcefields
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "openmmforcefields" %}
{% set version = "0.11.1" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/openmm/openmmforcefields/archive/{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 22a201ee31c2e3f35dda9937aa87ef279aa96f4d8fd73f63c656774a202b4aa0

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv --no-deps

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.6
    - pip
  run:
    - python >=3.6
    - openmm >=7.6.0
    - pyyaml
    - ambertools >=20.0
    - lxml
    - networkx
    - tinydb
    - openff-toolkit >=0.9.0
    - openff-forcefields >=1.2.0
    - validators

test:
  imports:
    - openmmforcefields

about:
  home: http://openmm.org/
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Extra support for additional forcefields in OpenMM
  description: |
    Support for AMBER and CHARMM force fields and small molecule
    parameterization with GAFF and the Open Force Field Toolkit
    for OpenMM.
  doc_url: http://docs.openmm.org/
  dev_url: https://github.com/openmm/openmmforcefields

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - jaimergp
    - jchodera
    - peastman
    - mikemhenry
    - ijpulidos
